class GUIFuzzer: A fuzzer for GUIs, using Selenium.

__init__(self, driver, *, miner: Optional[GUIGrammarMiner] = None, stay_on_host: bool = True, log_gui_exploration: bool = False, disp_gui_exploration: bool = False, **kwargs) -> None: Constructor. `driver` - the Selenium driver to use. `miner` - the miner to use (default: `GUIGrammarMiner(driver)`) `stay_on_host` - if True (default), do not explore external links. `log_gui_exploration` - if set, print out exploration steps. `disp_gui_exploration` - if set, display screenshot of current Web page as well as FSM diagrams during exploration. Other keyword arguments are passed to the `GrammarFuzzer` superclass.
restart(self) -> None: Get back to original URL
run(self, runner: GUIRunner) -> Tuple[str, str]: Run the fuzzer on the given GUIRunner `runner`.
fsm_last_state_symbol(self, tree: DerivationTree) -> str: Return current (expected) state symbol
fsm_path(self, tree: DerivationTree) -> List[str]: Return sequence of state symbols.
set_grammar(self, new_grammar: Dict[str, List[Expansion]]) -> None: Set grammar to `new_grammar`.
update_existing_state(self) -> None: Update actions of existing state
update_new_state(self) -> None: Found new state; extend grammar accordingly
update_state(self) -> None: Determine current state from current Web page
class GrammarFuzzer: Produce strings from grammars efficiently, using derivation trees.

__init__(self, grammar: Dict[str, List[Expansion]], start_symbol: str = '<start>', min_nonterminals: int = 0, max_nonterminals: int = 10, disp: bool = False, log: Union[bool, int] = False) -> None: Produce strings from `grammar`, starting with `start_symbol`. If `min_nonterminals` or `max_nonterminals` is given, use them as limits for the number of nonterminals produced. If `disp` is set, display the intermediate derivation trees. If `log` is set, show intermediate steps as text on standard output.
fuzz(self) -> str: Produce a string from the grammar.
fuzz_tree(self) -> DerivationTree: Produce a derivation tree from the grammar.
class Fuzzer: Base class for fuzzers.
__init__(self) -> None: Constructor
fuzz(self) -> str: Return fuzz input
run(self, runner: Fuzzer.Runner = <Fuzzer.Runner object>) -> Tuple[subprocess.CompletedProcess, str]: Run `runner` with fuzz input
runs(self, runner: Fuzzer.Runner = <Fuzzer.PrintRunner object>, trials: int = 10) -> List[Tuple[subprocess.CompletedProcess, str]]: Run `runner` with fuzz input, `trials` times
class GUICoverageFuzzer: Systematically explore all states of the current Web page
__init__(self, *args, **kwargs): Constructor. All args are passed to the `GUIFuzzer` superclass.
explore_all(self, runner: GUIRunner, max_actions=100) -> None: Explore all states of the GUI, up to `max_actions` (default 100).
class GrammarCoverageFuzzer: Produce from grammars, aiming for coverage of all expansions.
class SimpleGrammarCoverageFuzzer: When choosing expansions, prefer expansions not covered.
class TrackingGrammarCoverageFuzzer: Track grammar coverage during production

__init__(self, *args, **kwargs) -> None: Produce strings from `grammar`, starting with `start_symbol`. If `log` is set, show intermediate steps as text on standard output.
class GUIRunner: Execute the actions in a given action string
